						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying on the way to Maṇṇēri about a furlong from the village.</p>						

						<p>Circa 16th century.</p>						

						<p>This is dated the cyclic year Paridhāvi, Māgha śu. 11. The details cannot be verified.</p>						

						<p>It seems to record a gift of land by Timmarasa, the <hi rend="italic">Nāḍa-gauḍa</hi> of Dāṇakasiruūra when Kōna-Rāchayya was administering the tract.</p>						

						</summary>
